ZH: 他是个不诚实的人，经常说谎。
EN: He is not honest, he lies all the time.

ZH: 她在面试中不诚实地夸大了自己的能力。
EN: She dishonestly exaggerated her skills during the interview.

ZH: 作弊是不诚实的行为。
EN: Cheating is an act of dishonesty.

ZH: 你不能相信那个不诚实的销售代表。
EN: You can't trust that dishonest sales representative.

ZH: 不诚实的行为会破坏信任。
EN: Dishonest actions can destroy trust.

ZH: 我们的公司绝不容忍不诚实的员工。
EN: Our company does not tolerate dishonest employees.

ZH: 不诚实的行为将会受到惩罚。
EN: Dishonest behavior will be punished.

ZH: 写作文时，请务必保持诚实，不要抄袭。
EN: When writing an essay, make sure to be honest and not plagiarize.

ZH: 骗人是很不诚实的行为。
EN: Lying is a very dishonest behavior.

ZH: 总是说谎是不诚实的表现。
EN: Constantly lying is a sign of dishonesty.

ZH: 第一次沟通时，要保持诚实和透明。
EN: It's important to be honest and transparent during the first communication.

ZH: 不诚实的人最终会被揭露。
EN: Dishonest people will eventually be exposed.

ZH: 老师强调了诚实的重要性。
EN: The teacher emphasized the importance of honesty.

ZH: 他因为不诚实的行为被公司解雇了。
EN: He was fired from the company because of his dishonest behavior.

ZH: 对于不诚实的人，我们应该要有警惕。
EN: We should be vigilant towards dishonest people.

ZH: 不诚实的行为会损害你的声誉。
EN: Dishonest behavior can damage your reputation.

ZH: 他被指控欺骗，证明了他不诚实。
EN: He was accused of deception, proving his dishonesty.

ZH: 招聘时要警惕那些不诚实的求职者。
EN: Be cautious of dishonest job applicants during recruitment.

ZH: 不诚实的行为会给自己带来困难。
EN: Dishonest behavior will bring difficulties to oneself.

ZH: 他因为不诚实的态度失去了信任。
EN: He lost trust because of his dishonest attitude.
